<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>SPAN 364.  Acquisition of Spanish.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Examination of the psychological and social aspects of the acquisition of Spanish as a first language, a second language, and in bilingual contexts.  Prerequisite(s): Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=SPAN%20206" title="SPAN 206" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'SPAN 206');">SPAN 206</a>; and sophomore standing or above.<br/>
