<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>SPAN 376.  Topics in Politics, the Economy, and Law in Hispanic Culture.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Basic introduction to the syntax and rhetoric of legality, order and hierarchy in Spain and/or Latin America as these elements are manifested in literary and cultural texts. Course Information: May be repeated to a maximum of 6 hours, if topics vary, and with consent of the instructor. Prerequisite(s): Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=SPAN%20210" title="SPAN 210" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'SPAN 210');">SPAN 210</a>. Recommended background: Credit or concurrent registration in <a href="/search/?P=SPAN%20212" title="SPAN 212" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'SPAN 212');">SPAN 212</a>.<br/>
